title: Sandi beats Fyfe for Dockers club champion
text:
Ruckman Aaron Sandilands wins Fremantle Dockers club champion award Doig Medal BRADEN QUARTERMAINE PerthNow Ruckman Aaron Sandilands wins Fremantle Dockers club champion award Doig Medal BRADEN QUARTERMAINE PerthNow Aaron Sandilands has won the Fremantle Dockers’ club champion award, the Doig Medal. Picture: Justin Benson-Cooper 
CHAMPION Fremantle ruckman Aaron Sandilands claimed his second Doig Medal as Brownlow Medal winner Nat Fyfe was relegated to fourth in a dramatic count at Crown Perth. 
Fyfe’s four games missed through injury proved costly, as 32-year-old Sandilands cemented his reputation as one of the club’s greats by becoming the fourth multiple winner of the Doig Medal. 
Sandilands joined skipper Matthew Pavlich, former captain Peter Bell and Fyfe in that elite club. 
Having finished second to Fyfe last season, Sandilands won with 282 votes, edging out midfielder David Mundy by five votes. 
Stephen Hill finished third on 261 votes, one ahead of Fyfe, with Michael Walters rounding out the top five.
